[MK] cases #21CM387, #21CM436, #21CT362, #22CF143, #22CM65, #22CT124 called at 2:55pm 
Defendant Nathaniel S McGuire in court, in custody, with Attorney Karl Huebner. ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
____________________
Plea & Sentencing Hearing is held as to Cases #21CM436, #21CT362, #22CT124, #22CM65:
ADA Beck verifies victim rights compliance, submitting victim impact statements
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " Guilty " entered in Case #21CM436-count #4, and in Case #21CM65-Counts #1 & #2 ; factual basis stipulated.  The Court accepts the pleas, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Convictions entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses Case #21CM436-Counts #1, #2, #3; and the Court reads in (designating Case #21CM65 as the case these are being read-in to) the following:  Case #21CT362, Case #22CT124. Further the Court reads-in an uncharged referral for Bailjumping in connection with Case #22CT124 and thereafter bars further prosecution of that uncharged referral.

In Case #21CM436-Count #4 the Court sentences Mr. McGuire to:
--serve 20 days in Jefferson County Jail consecutive to any other sentence in being, with Huber privileges for work and treatment; to commence forthwith 
--0 days credit for time already served given at this point. Counsel may submit a stipulation as to days credit 
--pay costs plus DNA surcharge= $443.  The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office. Non-payment will result in a 20 day jail term with Huber privileges, consecutive
The Court orders DNA sample provision.
__________________
In Case 21CM65 on both Count #1 and Count #2 each the Court sentences Mr. McGuire to: 
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges for work and treatment
--0 days credit for time already served given at this point. Counsel may submit a stipulation as to days credit
The Court STAYS the sentences and places Mr. McGuire on Probation for one year, with conditions: 
--Mr. McGuire is not to own, possess or operate a motor vehicle 
--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling per Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program per Agent
--to comply with DNA sample provision

Separate from the conditions of Probation, the Court orders payment of costs plus DNA surcharges= $886. The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office. Non-payment will result in a 20 day jail term with Huber privileges, concurrent with the alternate sentence in case #21CM436 but consecutive to any other sentence.
